news.title: Properties within Lal Dora will be permitted to sell: Haryana's minister
news.para: Landowners can now directly register their properties without having to pay property tax or development fees. There are about 2,52,000 such properties in the state.

news.title: Signatureglobal (India)'s subsidiary buys 3.8 acres land in Gurugram
news.para: The said land has an overall potential developable area of approximate 6 lakh sq ft.

news.title: PNB Housing to consider proposal of fund raising up to Rs 10,000 crore
news.para: PNB Housing Finance's remuneration committee approved the grant of 50,000 Options representing 50,000 equity shares of Rs 10 each to eligible employee under ESOP Scheme II 2018 of the company.

news.title: Sobha's board approves Rs 2,000 crore right issue
news.para: Sobha's board approved 12,107,981 Rights Equity Shares each on partly-paid basis for an amount up to Rs 2,000 crore and rights issue price of Rs 1,651 per Rights Equity Share.

news.title: New committee appointed to study amendments to Maharashtra apartment ownership act
news.para: In October last year, a 15-member panel had submitted recommendations on the amendments. However, just after eight months, the state government has announced another committee.

news.title: Ambuja Cements acquires Penna Cement for Rs 10,422 crore
news.para: Ambuja Cements will acquire 100% shares of Penna Cement Industries from its existing promoter group, P. Pratap Reddy and family. The acquisition will be fully funded through internal accruals.

news.title: Puravankara board approves Rs 1,000 crore fundraising via QIP
news.para: Puravankara's wholly-owned subisidiary Provident Housing provided a corporate guarantee in favour of Piramal Enterprises for the purpose of meeting the cost of acquisition of ~31.8 acres of land parcel situated at Dabolim, Goa.

news.title: Fire in Kolkata rooftop restaurant raises concerns over building permits
news.para: Kolkata Municipal Corporation buildings department to send notice to owner of property at 1/1, Camac Street regarding conversion of terrace into restaurant. Fire in rooftop restaurant sparks scrutiny on similar conversions.

news.title: Tata Digital renews lease for headquarter Fort House in South Mumbai
news.para: The technology company that controls Bigbasket, Tata 1mg, Tata Cliq, Croma, and superapp Tata Neu among others will be paying rentals of nearly Rs 3 crore per month as per the agreement that stipulates lock-in period of one year.

news.title: Britain's Revolut picks new Canary Wharf headquarter
news.para: Revolut will take four floors of the building on a 10-year lease from May 2025, increasing its office footprint to 113,000 square feet after leaving its home in the north-west corner of the estate, the company said in a statement on Thursday.

news.title: Amazon to lease over 1.1 million sq ft in Bengaluru
news.para: Sattva Group has built a new office tower at Sattva Horizon business park near the international airport. The 11-storey building will be able to accommodate more than 7,000 employees, and Amazon will be the sole occupant.

news.title: Sebi to auction 19 properties of KBCL India in July
news.para: The regulator has initiated the process for the sale of assets after KBCL India Ltd, its directors Rakesh Kumar, Vishvnath Pratap Singh and Shashi Kant Mishra failed to refund the investors' money.

news.title: Kochi Metro Rail appoints NBCC as implementing agency for Bliss City project
news.para: KMRL has appointed National Buildings Construction Corporation (NBCC) as implementing agency for the development of Bliss City land at Kakkanad.

news.title: Jaypee Infratech appoints Devang Pravin Patel as CFO
news.para: Suraksha Group, which has taken control of Jaypee Infratech ltd (JIL) after approval from the appellate tribunal NCLAT last month, will delist JIL from stock exchanges.

news.title: Brigade Group to invest Rs 8,000 crore in Chennai by 2030
news.para: In FY25, Brigade Group plans to launch over three million sq ft of residential projects and about 1 million n sqft of commercial development in Chennai.

news.title: Adani Group is evaluating multiple cement companies for acquisition
news.para: The group is aggressively pursuing an inorganic strategy to boost capacity and emerge as the largest cement manufacturer within the next three to four years, overtaking the Aditya Birla Group’s UltraTech.

news.title: Orris Infrastructure vs Godrej Properties case reaches Delhi high court
news.para: The complainant, Orris Infrastructure, claimed in its plea before the court that Godrej Properties was supposed to pay Rs 202 crore for 10 acres of land for the project by Sept 2022 but had so far paid only Rs 37 crore.

news.title: Jaypee Infratech delisting: Suraksha Realty to pay exit price to retail shareholders
news.para: The successful resolution applicant of Jaypee Infratech will pay on a par with the liquidation value of the company to its shareholders holding about 542 million equity units while delisting the company from the stock exchanges.

news.title: China central bank says it will push relending for affordable housing
news.para: The central bank last month set up a 300 billion yuan ($41.4 billion) relending loan facility for affordable housing, and Wednesday's virtual meeting hosted from the city of Jinan in eastern Shandong province is the latest effort to promote the facility among local governments and banks.

news.title: Maharashtra government's slum policy strange as it encourages encroachments: Bombay HC
news.para: ​​In a judgement passed on Tuesday, a division bench of Justices Girish Kulkarni and Jitendra Jain said the state's policy has resulted in large pockets of land being siphoned out from the "state pool".
